{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block content %}

	<div class="intro_header">
		<div class="intro_title">YOUR EXPLORATION CO-PILOT!
			<p>Discover, Save & Share! Everything you need to prepare for your next quest!</p>
			<div class="intro_stats">
				We currently reference
				<b>{{pins}}</b>
				locations, in
				<b>{{country}}</b>
				countries and
				<b>{{type}}</b>
				categories.<br><br>
			</div>
			<div class="intro_button">
				<a class="intro_login" href="{% if app.user %}{{ path('app_location_index') }}{% else %}{{ path('app_login') }}{% endif %}">
					<i class="fa-solid fa-map-pin"></i>
					Create your Map !
				</a>
				
				<a class="intro_github" target="_blank" href="https://github.com/clementp0/a2urbex">
					<i class="fa-brands fa-github"></i>
					View the Source</a>
			</div>

		</div>
		<div class="intro_img"><img src="./home/home.png"></div>
	</div>
	{# ALL YOUR PINS #}
	<div class="home-content">
		<div class="home-content-image">
			<img src="./home/add.png">
		</div>
		<div class="home-content-text">
			<h1>Add your pins !
			</h1>
			<p class="home-content-text-p">Choose a category, enter the coordinates, import your image... and THAT'S IT! Countries, Waze and Maps are automatically generated! You can also edit and delete your Pins (you can even add a comment like "Oops... cops at the entrance")</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	{# LOOK AT YOUR MAP #}
	<div class="home-content">
		<div class="home-content-text">
			<h1>Look at your map
			</h1>
			<p class="home-content-text-p right">All the Pins you've created are available on the map with an icon representing their category. You can also click on the pin of your choice to preview it (and access all the information and links like Waze or Maps!)</p>
		</div>
		<div class="home-content-image">
			<img src="./home/map.png">
		</div>
	</div>
	{# SHARE WITH YOUR FRIENDS  #}
	<div class="home-content">
		<div class="home-content-image">
			<img src="./home/favorites.png">
		</div>
		<div class="home-content-text">
			<h1>Share with your friends!
			</h1>
			<p class="home-content-text-p">You can add your friends and see their pins on your map! Create collaborative lists and share them with your friends or make them public to share with your travel partners outside the website!</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	{# A2URBEX #}
	<div class="home-content">
		<div class="home-content-text">
			<h1>Who are we?
			</h1>
			<p class="home-content-text-p right"></p>
			<p class="adeux">
				<i class="fa-brands fa-instagram"></i>
				Follow us on instagram<a target="blank" href="https://www.instagram.com/a2urbex/">
					@a2urbex</a>
			</p>
			<p class="home_urbex">
				Nice to meet you! We are
				<a target="blank" href="https://www.instagram.com/clement.po/">@clement.po</a>
				and
				<a target="blank" href="https://www.instagram.com/hugolahaxe/">
					@hugolahaxe</a>, two web developers from Bordeaux but above all two urban explorers for many years. We created this platform to simplify our expeditions... but after months of coding and adding features to it, it would have been selfish of us not to share it with other enthusiasts!
			</p>
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="home-content-image">
		<a href="https://youtu.be/HEW0atdGn4A" target="_blank">
			<img src="./home/video.png">
		</a>
	</div>
</div>
{# PRICE #}
<div class="home-content">
	<div class="home-content-image">
		<img src="./home/github.png">
	</div>
	<div class="home-content-text">
		<h1>Is it free?
		</h1>
		<p class="home-content-text-p">Yup! 100% free, we do not charge anything for the use of this platform. As we said above, it was originally designed to simplify our travels. But we want to share it with everyone. That's why anyone can access our site and use it as they see fit. (We also provide all our source code) Enjoy!</p>
	</div>
</div>
{# Mobile #}
<div class="home-content">
	<div class="home-content-text">
		<h1>Anywhere!
		</h1>
		<p class="home-content-text-p right">You can use it while exploring! Everything is designed to be used on your phone, a simple and accessible interface. All with a dark theme (because who wants to be caught for the brightness of their phone?). Click on the Waze/Maps links to start your journey! You can also install the web app for a minimal data usage! (Useful in our lost countryside).</p>
	</div>
	<div class="home-content-image">
		<img src="./home/mobile.png">
	</div>
</div></div>{% endblock %}
